					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720#post-4161219</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720/scp-3749#post-4161219</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 22 Feb 2019 06:39:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I figure it'd be a major pain in the ass to do a test involving a single microbe. Ultimately though, I just didn't personally think any of those things would add enough value to make them worth including.</p> <blockquote> <p>So much was said in just a few words.</p> </blockquote> <p>That's one of the best compliments someone could give my writing ^_^</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720#post-4161116</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720/scp-3749#post-4161116</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 22 Feb 2019 04:10:08 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Steaming</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>399979</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think it's a great start but it needs more, perhaps an experiment log? You put it into a sterile environment with a few living things and see what happens:</p> <p>- Normal Air - It justs spins in circles trying to kill all bacteria<br /> - One microbe and one human - Which does it go after first? What if one is closer than the other?<br /> - A virus. This is the interesting one to me since not everyone considers viruses to be alive.<br /> - A murderer human and an innocent baby - does it care about morals?</p> <p>Also, that 'after some difficulty, it was contained' line made me laugh. So much was said in just a few words.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720#post-4159246</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10281720/scp-3749#post-4159246</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 20 Feb 2019 09:57:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ikonovich</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1614162</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Nah, any average room contains tens of millions of bacteria on the low end, and humans pump them out constantly. With a good draft of regular ambient air you can almost certainly introduce bacteria faster than this thing can kill them, effectively containing it by default.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
